  },
  "source_transcript_segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.6,
      "text": "Want a plan that actually works?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.6,
      "end": 4.32,
      "text": "Let me show you in three simple actionable steps."
    },
    {
      "start": 4.32,
      "end": 6.56,
      "text": "Step one, define the true target."
    },
    {
      "start": 6.56,
      "end": 8.16,
      "text": "Most people write down goals."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.16,
      "end": 10.8,
      "text": "They sound inspiring, but they're not precise."
    },
    {
      "start": 10.8,
      "end": 13.04,
      "text": "Here's what the top 1% do differently."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.04,
      "end": 14.56,
      "text": "They define a true target."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.56,
      "end": 17.6,
      "text": "One specific outcome with a non-negotiable deadline,"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.6,
      "end": 19.44,
      "text": "such as not to grow on YouTube,"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.44,
      "end": 22.32,
      "text": "but upload two videos a week for the next 30 days,"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.32,
      "end": 25.92,
      "text": "not get fit, but lose three kilograms by August 1st."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.37,
      "end": 32.01,
      "text": "first. Step two, know your X and Y. Now comes what almost nobody does, the breakdown of the target."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.92,
      "end": 26.56,
      "text": "Step two,"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.01,
      "end": 37.21,
      "text": "Most people just plan for if everything goes right, but success is built on anticipating"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.21,
      "end": 42.73,
      "text": "what goes wrong. So list every obstacle you'll face. Use this formula. If you have X obstacle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.73,
      "end": 47.85,
      "text": "then you'll tackle it with action Y and you should always anticipate your X and create your Ys."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.85,
      "end": 52.65,
      "text": "For example, if I get an urge to eat a cheat meal during my fat loss journey, I'll grab a low calorie"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.65,
      "end": 54.17,
      "text": "snack instead. Step three,"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.96,
      "end": 57.68,
      "text": "instead. Step three, anchor and activate. This is the most ignored but crucial step,"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.68,
      "end": 62.32,
      "text": "the one that turns your plan into a ritual. Most people make a plan and expect willpower"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.32,
      "end": 66.96,
      "text": "to do the rest. But top performers don't rely on memory. They install the plan into their daily"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.96,
      "end": 72.0,
      "text": "flow using two tools, anchors and reminders. An anchor is any action you already do every day,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.0,
      "end": 76.8,
      "text": "brushing your teeth, drinking coffee, opening your laptop. You attach your plan to that moment."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.29,
      "end": 80.61,
      "text": "moment. Example, right after I brush my teeth I look at my three step plan. A"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.8,
      "end": 77.68,
      "text": "Example, write a"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.61,
      "end": 83.97,
      "text": "reminder is about external accountability because memory fades and"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.97,
      "end": 88.09,
      "text": "motivation drops. You need external triggers. Use sticky notes, calendar"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.09,
      "end": 92.25,
      "text": "events, even ask a friend to check in. The goal is to create a trigger plus"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.25,
      "end": 95.93,
      "text": "ping system that makes your plan"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.664,
      "end": 94.824,
      "text": "system that makes your plan unavoidable."
    }
  ],
